sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the execution of a Windows system binary that is usually located in the system folder from an uncommon location.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Florian Roth (Nextron Systems), Patrick Bareiss, Anton Kutepov, oscd.community, Nasreddine Bencherchali (Nextron Systems)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Use Short Name Path in Command Line
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detect use of the Windows 8.3 short name. Which could be used as a method to avoid command-line detection
Detects the Setting of Windows Defender Exclusions

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: New Firewall Rule Added Via Netsh.EXE
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the addition of a new rule to the Windows firewall via netsh

match_context.values: @{CommandLine="C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Host-process for services of Windows" dir=in action=allow program="C:\Windows\system32\svchost.exe" enable=yes>nul; Image=C:\Windows\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}

@{CommandLine="%windir%\System32\netsh.exe" advfirewall firewall add rule name="Host-process for services of Windows" dir=in action=allow program="%windir%\SysWOW64\svchost.exe" enable=yes>nul; Image=%windir%\System32\netsh.exe; EventID=1}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects modification of autostart extensibility point (ASEP) in registry.
sigma_analysis_results.rule_author: Victor Sergeev, Daniil Yugoslavskiy, Gleb Sukhodolskiy, Timur Zinniatullin, oscd.community, Tim Shelton, frack113 (split)

sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of a new service using the "sc.exe" utility.

match_context.values: @{CommandLine="C:\Windows\System32\sc.exe" create bfuukaaa binPath= "C:\Windows\system32\bfuukaaa\wmmjvhxv.exe /d\"c:\analyse\1724206214.907292_b42326c3-9eb0-4e7a-8992-a02c6f9ada47\"" type= own start= auto DisplayName= "wifi support"; Image=C:\Windows\System32\sc.exe; EventID=1}

@{CommandLine="%windir%\System32\sc.exe" create lzciitih binPath= "%windir%\SysWOW64\lzciitih\tiahmkph.exe /d\"%SAMPLEPATH%\"" type= own start= auto DisplayName= "wifi support"; Image=%windir%\System32\sc.exe; EventID=1}
